Events.Title: Art Wall and MORE
Events.Description: Come decorate or art wall!  leave a little touch of you as you pass.  Our art wall sheets will become a forever part of our camp to show the world the inclusing art brings!

Events.Title: Djembejam
Events.Description: After a late breakfast, mosey on by for a one on one djembe jam. From first-timers to old pros, we'll go at the pace you dictate. Bring your own drum or use ours. Fifteen minute sessions (unless nobody is waiting). You'll learn mama, papa, three kookoo parts or just settle in for a blissful rhythmic exchange. After all, there is no drama, mon. Hippies welcome (just don't tell anyone).

Events.Title: Found & Lost*
Events.Description:
*Not a typo!
The Official Unofficial L&F @ LoF!
Found an item and don't know where it belongs? We'll try to find out!
Lost an item and aren't sure where to find it? We may have it or know who has it! Seek out or return items after the event via http://bit.ly/2pNJKUF

Events.Title: BBQ & Community Smoker
Events.Description: The dcbbq will smoke and gift hundreds of pounds of delicious BBQ during LoF.  Look for the "Meat Wagon" cruising around the event.  Rules: The BBQ is ready whenever it's ready, and allow us to serve. Our dedicated community smoker is back in 2017 for use by the LoF community! Basic orientation is required; swing by camp and find Dev or an authorized dcbbq agent. Rules: We will not babysit your food, and we will not accept "donations" of unwanted meat/food. Brisket.

Events.Title: Beer O?Clock at the Thirsty Sphinx
Events.Description: Keep an eye out for the sign at the Thirsty Sphinx Bar! When the planets align and a Sphinx bartender emerges from the cosmos, the sign will go up at our bar and the sweet brewed nectar will flow! Bring your cup to share in the Sphinx?s liquid bounty - non-alcoholic beverages will also be offered.

Events.Title: BIG GIANT TETHER BALL
Events.Description:
YOU?VE SEE IT!
YOU?VE PLAYED IT!
IT?S BACK!
BIG GIANT TETHER BALL 
Look for it at a beach near you by the Tiki Bar

Events.Title: BIG ISLAND TIKI BAR & BIG KAHUNA FLOATING BAR
Events.Description:
Our exotic themed drinking establishment will serve elaborate cocktails. So put on your best Hawaiian shirt for an extra surprise and Hula on over to our Tiki Bar or Float around at the Big Kahuna Bar. 
A Tropical Blast and a Splash, Splash! 
Open times will vary

Events.Title: Brand New Buddy Bench
Events.Description:
Looking for a new buddy? Not sure what to do? Come make a new buddy at the Brand New Buddy Bench!

It's simple! Hover near it; sit, stand, dance! Wait for someone else to hover, too! When they do, FAH-DAH, a BNB! 

There will be a WWW with one of those AM/PM device things, some of those weird ice breaking questions (Not you Ice Nation, BNB ice), and of course a table for you to set your cup on and forget it, so you can come back and make ANOTHER BRAND NEW BUDDY!

Events.Title: Bubble Bar
Events.Description: Over in Hullabaloo Village the crews from Scrubby's Angels and The Fort will be mixing some bubbly concoctions to wet your whistle, we specialize in cocktails mixed with  your favorite Michigan mixers. Our bar will be open during all posted Hullabaloo, Scrubby's Angels, and Fort events. Join us for a nighttime dance party or random hammock hanging afternoons.You never know what might be poppin' at the Bubble Bar.   BYOC (Bring your own cup).

Events.Title: Burner Blanket Painting
Events.Description: Stop by and decorate a blanket for a burner in need! Did you forget your blanket? Need something warm to snuggle in? Stop by and we will provide you with an awesome gift from your burner family.

Events.Title: Canned Ham Camp
Events.Description:
It's all about the ham.  We eat ham, we live in a ham, we love ham.
Our camp is centered on our 1957 Classic Canned Ham Camper.  Please pay us a visit and we'll give you a tour.

Events.Title: Casual Misfortune Telling
Events.Description: The Gypsies are most EXCELLENT at telling your misfortune! Stop on by anytime we're in camp and request to have your runes interpreted, your palm read, your cards deciphered. Remember that we are professionals and definitely NOT just making random stuff up about you for our own amusements.

Events.Title: Gallery In The Pines
Events.Location: Pine Forest between Gate and Greeters
Events.Description: Gallery in the Pines is an interactive community art gallery featuring artwork of all kinds - by our own community! Located in the Art Hub pine forest near the entrance to Lakes of Fire. Featuring the Dead Letter Office and the Memorial Room (an installation to honor those who have passed away.)
Events.HumanLocation: Pine Forest between Gate and Greeters

Events.Title: Gaming With The Gods
Events.Description: Stop in any time to join a table or yard game of your choice. Table games will be under the tent and yard games by the bar; come while away an hour in play!

Events.Title: GiGi
Events.Description:
GiGi, formerly incarnated as the Celestial Firefly, will be returning in a new form this year.
What will it be?
We don't even really know.
Watch the lake; watch for flames and we'll both find out.

Events.Title: Lounge of the Gods
Events.Description: The Lounge has expanded with more space to recline and rest your weary warrior bones upon the lush fur-covered inflatable. Fellow Vikings will tell you the tales of the heroes and gods of days gone by while you sip mugs of glogg, and prepare for Ragnarok by sharpening your skills at hammerschlagen.

Events.Title: Love, Light, Music, More
Events.Description: Stop by Lux Ephemera during the day to fill your cups with floral-essence waters [we plan on offering Rose and Neroli], make a buddy, or just hang out in our lawn.  Come back and see us in the dark, though... we transform into a rainbowlightshinelovetimemusicshrine... we think it's worth checking out.  WE LOVE YOU!

Events.Title: Mama Boodles' Spunyun Hut
Events.Description: And so it came that Mama Boodles befriended the Ice Fairies, providing them a comfortable home to rest and frolic upon the shores of Lucky Lake. Using her interdimensional powers, Mama Boodles created a series of nesting hexayurts for her newfound minions, allowing them a peaceful respite from the Grand Climate War, and a convenient way to "recruit" new fairies, as well... Enter at your own risk...

Events.Title: Port Authority Camp
Events.Description:
Port Authority is a group dedicated to promoting boating and general water safety at Lakes of Fire. 
The "Pink PFD" program this year will place personal flotation devices and life vests at strategic locations around the lake for all to use. Boaters are reminded that every passenger on board your vessel must have access to a flotation device according to Michigan boating law.
The Lake is our Playa.
An informational booth will be located at the LOF Yacht Club. Stop by and learn more about what you can do to help.
Any supplies you can donate are much appreciated.
Events.HumanLocation: LoF Yacht Club (or find Pirate) | Site 35

Events.Title: Rights of Passage
Events.Description: The pooparazzi is back for a second year! Find us here, there, any where near a porta potty! We are here to celebrate your bodily functions! Are you lucky enough to feel poopular?

Events.Title: Schnapps Shots Detour
Events.Description: Stop in for a sweet tasty shot of homemade schnapps, have a Native American Medicine card reading.  Be on the lookout  for the minibar and Camp Mascot!

Events.Title: Sphinx?s Menagerie
Events.Description: Come borrow a trusty steed from our floaty corral to aid you on your lake-bound adventures! We?ll be offering all manner of beasties for your buoyancy assistance needs. We do ask that you kindly return your creature to its paddock for the night when you?ve finished your aquatic cavorting.

Events.Title: Take a Book, Leave a Book
Events.Description: Browse the books of the Lucky Lake Burner Library and choose a textual friend to take home and cuddle. (We do mean books!) Or, chat with a librarian, get a book recommendation, or take a stern shushin' for the road.
Events.HumanLocation: Lucky Lake Burner Library | Site K11

Events.Title: The Flow Project
Events.Description:
The Flow Project is setup to provide a welcoming space both visually and musically for participants to express their flow; whether it be dancing, spinning fire/hoops/poi, or what have you.. Our user friendly Flow Stage, stripper pole optional, will be available for open use. White gas will be provided for participants as a gift, as well as safeties if need be. Although we encourage radical self reliance. 

DJs will be spinning night and day. Chill vibes by day full on rager style vibes by night. Come kick it with us!!

Events.Title: The Huggery
Events.Description: Hugs served fresh and hot all day every day. Looking for that special hug for you or a friend? Come and visit the Huggery! We have an extensive menu of classic and specialty hugs as well as daily specials. Don't see what you want? Make a request and we'll do our best to fulfill it! Nobody is at the Huggery when you get there? You're hired! Step around to the other side of the counter and give out dem hugs!

Events.Title: Theme Camp Capture The Flag Creation & Registration
Events.Description: Do you have a flag? No? Participants of the 2017 LOF Capture the Flag game will need to create their camp flag at the Camp Flag Creation Station. What? You DO have a flag? Well then come registration so that when the games begin we know whose camp flag to steal and whose dirty undies we leave hanging on the trees.

Events.Title: The Ravishing Rose Suite
Events.Description: Hospitality. Luxury. A retreat from the oontz-oontz. Air Burn~n~Burn aims to offer two Lucky Lake citizens a stay in our Ravishing Rose Suite each night. Winners will be chosen by drawing and are invited at dusk for a turndown service and a stay in our luxury suite surrounded by roses and fairy lights in a bedroom all their own. Upon their waking, they will be treated to breakfast. Leave feeling pampered and renewed, or at least well rested and well fed. After housekeeping changes the linens and restores cleanliness, the room will be open for another night.

Events.Title: Weegodda Village on display...
Events.Description: Weegodda lotta fun stuff this year!  Come chill out in *Igloo Obscura*, make a wish at The Wishing Well (until it burns Friday night), take pictures with friends at our updated LoF Dream Teams mural and fill up your water bottle at the Hydration Station!!

Events.Title: Gothic Coffee
Events.Description: Join the Gothee House for good company, goth/industrial dance music, and fresh hot coffee, dark like our souls. Coffee is served from early afternoon through the witching hour. Visitors are advised against signing contracts with magical creatures or following ghostly women into the woods.

Events.Title: The Syn Bar
Events.Description: Syncytium bar open daily from 2pm until 2am.  Beer and various mixed drinks.  Mixed drinks change daily.  Note: We are closed during the eggify burn.

Events.Title: Igloo Obscura demonstration
Events.Description: Stop by Igloo Obscura to learn about the concept of *camera obscura* and how it works.

Events.Title: Tyler the Typhoon?s Flow Warrior Congregation
Events.Description: Join Tyler the Typhoon of the hoop tribe  and come meet fellow flow warriors. Share your moves and techniques. This will be a great time to express your love for the power of flow! Any flow props are welcome! The more the merrier.

Events.Title: Dragon Dick?s House of Happy Endings
Events.Description: Here at Valhalla we are proud of our Dragon Dick?s titillating finger strokes. Come on over and just relax. Dragon Dick will do the rest. *Maybe longer if the Dragon Dick can keep it up.

Events.Title: Open Arts and Crafts
Events.Description: Within Sally the Sauropod you will find supplies for all your arts and crafts needs. We will have dinosaur themed coloring sheets, construction paper, glue sticks, craft scissors, crayons, pens, and colored pencils. Come drop by when you need to get some art time in.

Events.Title: Snickering Tick la Taberno
Events.Description: Come spin the rueda and play our fun juegos! Tick Town te ama!  ALSO: PoliTICKS got you down? Feeling frustrated? We have just the TICKet!  Come smash our pi�atas!  We'll be hosting this event daily around siesta time! You won't want to miss it! ALSO ALSO: LaTicka Canta-longs are new this year, so come on down and join in!  These flash mob pop up sing-a-longs have been inspired by our infamous Ticker-Twirl "sing a song" category.  We're taking it to a whole new level!  Happening throughout each day and night!

Events.Title: DIY Tattoo Station
Events.Description: Drink & Stitch is bring some supplies to make You the art! An interactive piece in which we supply the rubber stamps & ink and you are the canvas. The table will be set up in front of Village Not Sure each day whenever one of us sobers up enough to do so. It will remain in place till dark for your enjoyment.

Events.Title: Wednesday Bloody Mary Happy Hour
Events.Description: Come tell us about your work day over Bloody Marys served until we run out of ingredients.

Events.Title: Spanks & Dranks
Events.Description:
Come by Camp Safehouse  for some carnal fun mixed with libations.

We will be offering spankings from a variety of paddles, crops, whips and other  objects of punishment.  Or maybe you would like to be tied or placed in the stocks.  Whatever your kink or curiosity level we can handle it!
 There will be a wide and varied selection of spirits so come on out and join us.
Events.HumanLocation: Camp Pleasure / Camp Safehouse | Site F

Events.Title: Lakes of Fire Newbie Orientation
Events.Description: You've memorized the 10 Principles and read the entire survival guide (twice). Now, finally, you've arrived at Lakes of Fire. We're so glad you are here! Do you want some help getting the lay of the land? Have some burning questions you'd like answered? Your Greeter leads are thrilled to welcome you home, give you some tips, answer your questions and help set you on the path to awesome.

Events.Title: Raw Deal:  Mystic Tarot Roundtable
Events.Description:
Mystical Mike and Will Love will lead a group discussion on the Mystical Tarot-- what it is, how it is used, where it came from and why it's a valuable tool for self exploration.  The Tarot is pictorial encyclopedia of human existence, and it works both on a practical and a mystical level.  
If you have a lot of Tarot experience, please come and share; if you are new or beginning the Tarot, come and learn.

Events.Title: Irradiated Radio with Gorilla
Events.Description: Your favorite consistently distracted and awkward DJ, Gorilla, returns for a third year of avant garde jams that just about anybody can groove to! Some radio shows may claim to melt your face off with their so-called "hot mixes", but we deliver on that promise! Seriously, you might want to consider some protective headgear (maybe like a welding mask or something?).

Events.Title: Music Jam
Events.Description: Wishing you could jam at LOF but couldn't fit your drum kit/keyboard/guitar/bass/amps/etc in the car with all of the burner crap you brought this year?  No worries friends, we did the schlepping for you!  This is an open jam for musicians of all interests and ability levels.  There will be myriad electric and acoustic instruments available for use on our fully mic'ed stage.  Come jam with us!

Events.Title: Soma Activation for High Potential of Sacrament Activation (sunset yoga)
Events.Description: Bend your body and still your mind to ground in frequencies of expansion and receiving the highest potential from your experience at Lakes of Fire. We will prepare with breath, sun salutations, partner stretch, group mandala formation, and inner listening.

Events.Title: Green Dragon lounge opens
Events.Description: Come and chill in the Green Dragon lounge  Jams till sundown Deep dark ultra lounge till morning

Events.Title: Steak Cake n Booty Shake
Events.Location: The Consortium of Indigent Mythological Creatures and Imaginary Bunnies
Events.Description:
We'll bring the Steaks,  and the lil cakes!  We'll even make yer booty shake.  
Come celebrate Toki's birthday with us.
Events.HumanLocation: The Consortium of Indigent Mythological Creatures and Imaginary Bunnies | Site C

Events.Title: Well intentioned people....Bad medical advice.
Events.Description:
Crocked Docs versus Worse Nurses will gladly tell you what to do about your malady or condition in an OFF-DUTY alcoholish environment....(Think drunk history meets medicine) 
It will be wrong, sometimes painful and occasionally quite pleasurable and uplifting.The lovely ESD Volunteers will happily perform on the spot exams and intrusive procedures upon request and we keep our stethoscopes in the cooler (That'll perk up those buttons!) 
**all HIPPA rules apply to whatever happens or is discussed in this den of debauchery....no worries

Events.Title: Drunken sunset yoga
Events.Description: Find us! We will be drunk, somewhere, around sunset, everyday, doing yoga.

Events.Title: Hyperdrive Spacetime: Paradox Jukebox
Events.Description: Making your cosmic commute just a little more bearable, Doc Paradox brings you tomorrow's hits yesterday. Join Doc and his lovable cast of characters for two hours of radio from the future (weather and wormholes permitting).

Events.Title: Pyrosonica
Events.Description:
Pyrosonica is an ancient fire key thought to be lost eons ago. The key is only activated with certain magical tones, with each different tone unlocking another icy door in this realm. It has been entrusted to the inhabitants of "Hullabaloo Village" to make certain all revelers have full access to these Firey and Icy lands....
Come to "Hullabaloo Village" to warm yourself by the fire key in its activated state after dark and marvel at the display.

Events.Title: Sorr'eh Bar
Events.Description: Come order a cocktail from a friendly Canadian at Sorr'eh Bar.  You may or may not get what you ordered, you may even have to drink from a boot or a fish, we may or may not be able to identify what you are drinking...we're Sorr'eh.  We promise to apologize for anything that happens, so come drink with us!!

Events.Title: Frozen Kraken Floats
Events.Description: Frozen Kraken Creamery will be taking over Syncitium's bar to sling our cream down your throats! Come out and quench your thirst with optionally-alcoholic Rootbeer Floats.

Events.Title: It's gonna be a Bitchin' Kegger, Bro!
Events.Description: Come on over to Pick Dickle and have some dickleback shots. Eat some deep-fried pickles. Drink some award winning keg beer, bro. Do a keg stand even, see if we care! (We don't, just don't knock over the keg) We're gonna get that one dude to put on his spotify for us. I hear he's got the best party playlist on campus, bro! So pop your collar, dust off that puka shell necklace, come over, do shots, drink beer, and eat pickles. It'll be fun. Jager bombs! \m/

Events.Title: Mysterious Soul Bearing Shadow Shroud of Dancing Like No One Is Watching
Events.Description: The name says it all! There will be lights. There will be sounds. There will be big red buttons. What do the big red buttons do? Come find out! While you?re here bust a move and show me what you got.  Express yourself and bear your soul from behind the curtain where no one can see you, but everyone can watch your shadow jive.

Events.Description: You are all part of a fascinating experiment, an acid test.

If the stars align and paths cross, there may even be an opportunity to have your Tarot read by one of our residents!

Events.Title: Found In the Wild Erotica Contests
Events.Description:
Burners will be able to submit excerpts from published erotica matching daily themes. People will be able to wander by at their leisure before voting closes to vote on what tales are their favorites and best fit the themes to choose the winner of a small prize. Please have the author's name or username and the name of the piece written on the back of your excerpt. Also, please do not bring your own work for the contests. It is surely masterful and it would be unfair!

Events.Title: Burner Blanket Painting
Events.Description: Stop by and decorate a blanket for a burner in need! Did you forget your blanket? Need something warm to snuggle in? Stop by and we will provide you with an awesome gift from your burner family.

Events.Title: Canned Ham Camp
Events.Description:
It's all about the ham.  We eat ham, we live in a ham, we love ham.
Our camp is centered on our 1957 Classic Canned Ham Camper.  Please pay us a visit and we'll give you a tour.

Events.Title: Casual Misfortune Telling
Events.Description: The Gypsies are most EXCELLENT at telling your misfortune! Stop on by anytime we're in camp and request to have your runes interpreted, your palm read, your cards deciphered. Remember that we are professionals and definitely NOT just making random stuff up about you for our own amusements.

Events.Title: Compliment Tastings
Events.Description: Swing by the Lounge whenever you like and receive the compliment of your dreams. Our menu provides a variety of Compliment styles, sure to lift your spirits or leave you totally confused.

Events.Title: Desert Oasis Tea and Hookah Pit Stop
Events.Description:
Thirsty? Need a Pick-me-up or someone to talk to? Stop by our pit stop to refuel and relax, before continuing on your journey. Throughout the days, we will offer up some tea or start a session of hookah. You are more than welcome to join us and take in the views!

If the stars align and paths cross, there may even be an opportunity to have your Tarot read by one of our residents!

Events.Title: Found In the Wild Erotica Contests
Events.Description:
Burners will be able to submit excerpts from published erotica matching daily themes. People will be able to wander by at their leisure before voting closes to vote on what tales are their favorites and best fit the themes to choose the winner of a small prize. Please have the author's name or username and the name of the piece written on the back of your excerpt. Also, please do not bring your own work for the contests. It is surely masterful and it would be unfair!

Theme of the Day:

Thursday: Bodice Ripper
Friday: Paranormal
Saturday: Science Fiction
Events.HumanLocation: Lucky Lake Burner Library | Site K11

Events.Title: Gallery In The Pines
Events.Location: Pine Forest between Gate and Greeters
Events.Description: Gallery in the Pines is an interactive community art gallery featuring artwork of all kinds - by our own community! Located in the Art Hub pine forest near the entrance to Lakes of Fire. Featuring the Dead Letter Office and the Memorial Room (an installation to honor those who have passed away.)
Events.HumanLocation: Pine Forest between Gate and Greeters

Events.Title: Gaming With The Gods
Events.Description: Stop in any time to join a table or yard game of your choice. Table games will be under the tent and yard games by the bar; come while away an hour in play!

Events.Title: GiGi
Events.Description:
GiGi, formerly incarnated as the Celestial Firefly, will be returning in a new form this year.
What will it be?
We don't even really know.
Watch the lake; watch for flames and we'll both find out.

Events.Title: Hookah and Tea at The Den
Events.Description: Stop by and chill with us at The Den. We will periodically serve tea and offer hookah. Relax with calming light and music, and check out the compliment lounge while you're here!

Events.Title: Lounge of the Gods
Events.Description: The Lounge has expanded with more space to recline and rest your weary warrior bones upon the lush fur-covered inflatable. Fellow Vikings will tell you the tales of the heroes and gods of days gone by while you sip mugs of glogg, and prepare for Ragnarok by sharpening your skills at hammerschlagen.

Events.Title: Love, Light, Music, More
Events.Description: Stop by Lux Ephemera during the day to fill your cups with floral-essence waters [we plan on offering Rose and Neroli], make a buddy, or just hang out in our lawn.  Come back and see us in the dark, though... we transform into a rainbowlightshinelovetimemusicshrine... we think it's worth checking out.  WE LOVE YOU!

Events.Title: Mama Boodles' Spunyun Hut
Events.Description: And so it came that Mama Boodles befriended the Ice Fairies, providing them a comfortable home to rest and frolic upon the shores of Lucky Lake. Using her interdimensional powers, Mama Boodles created a series of nesting hexayurts for her newfound minions, allowing them a peaceful respite from the Grand Climate War, and a convenient way to "recruit" new fairies, as well... Enter at your own risk...

Events.Title: Open Arts and Crafts
Events.Description: Within Sally the Sauropod you will find supplies for all your arts and crafts needs. We will have dinosaur themed coloring sheets, construction paper, glue sticks, craft scissors, crayons, pens, and colored pencils. Come drop by when you need to get some art time in.

Events.Title: Port Authority Camp
Events.Description:
Port Authority is a group dedicated to promoting boating and general water safety at Lakes of Fire. 
The "Pink PFD" program this year will place personal flotation devices and life vests at strategic locations around the lake for all to use. Boaters are reminded that every passenger on board your vessel must have access to a flotation device according to Michigan boating law.
The Lake is our Playa.
An informational booth will be located at the LOF Yacht Club. Stop by and learn more about what you can do to help.
Any supplies you can donate are much appreciated.
Events.HumanLocation: LoF Yacht Club (or find Pirate) | Site 35

Events.Title: Rights of Passage
Events.Description: The pooparazzi is back for a second year! Find us here, there, any where near a porta potty! We are here to celebrate your bodily functions! Are you lucky enough to feel poopular?

Events.Title: RVB camp games!
Events.Description: Red vs Blue camp games. Whether team Red or Blue the competition is fierce! Try fowling, balance games, board games, all the games.

Events.Title: Schnapps Shots Detour
Events.Description: Stop in for a sweet tasty shot of homemade schnapps, have a Native American Medicine card reading.  Be on the lookout  for the minibar and Camp Mascot!

Events.Title: Sphinx?s Menagerie
Events.Description: Come borrow a trusty steed from our floaty corral to aid you on your lake-bound adventures! We?ll be offering all manner of beasties for your buoyancy assistance needs. We do ask that you kindly return your creature to its paddock for the night when you?ve finished your aquatic cavorting.

Events.Title: Strip With Style!
Events.Description: You look great with your clothes on, and great with your clothes off. Learn to look great in between, because it's hard to impress the cutie in the camp next door with your foot caught in your pant leg. No clothing is too strange. If you can put it on, Burnlesque's own Action will show you how to take it off. You can find him at the Burnlesque Camp, or wandering around Lucky Lake throughout the event.

Events.Title: Take a Book, Leave a Book
Events.Description: Browse the books of the Lucky Lake Burner Library and choose a textual friend to take home and cuddle. (We do mean books!) Or, chat with a librarian, get a book recommendation, or take a stern shushin' for the road.
Events.HumanLocation: Lucky Lake Burner Library | Site K11

Events.Title: The Flow Project
Events.Description:
The Flow Project is setup to provide a welcoming space both visually and musically for participants to express their flow; whether it be dancing, spinning fire/hoops/poi, or what have you.. Our user friendly Flow Stage, stripper pole optional, will be available for open use. White gas will be provided for participants as a gift, as well as safeties if need be. Although we encourage radical self reliance. 

DJs will be spinning night and day. Chill vibes by day full on rager style vibes by night. Come kick it with us!!

Events.Title: The Huggery
Events.Description: Hugs served fresh and hot all day every day. Looking for that special hug for you or a friend? Come and visit the Huggery! We have an extensive menu of classic and specialty hugs as well as daily specials. Don't see what you want? Make a request and we'll do our best to fulfill it! Nobody is at the Huggery when you get there? You're hired! Step around to the other side of the counter and give out dem hugs!

Events.Title: The Ravishing Rose Suite
Events.Description: Hospitality. Luxury. A retreat from the oontz-oontz. Air Burn~n~Burn aims to offer two Lucky Lake citizens a stay in our Ravishing Rose Suite each night. Winners will be chosen by drawing and are invited at dusk for a turndown service and a stay in our luxury suite surrounded by roses and fairy lights in a bedroom all their own. Upon their waking, they will be treated to breakfast. Leave feeling pampered and renewed, or at least well rested and well fed. After housekeeping changes the linens and restores cleanliness, the room will be open for another night.

Events.Title: The Shady Pussy Biergarten
Events.Description: Lounge in the Shady Pussy Biergarten . We?ll have homebrew, gin punch & Sangria. BYOC (bring your cup).

Events.Title: Weegodda Village on display...
Events.Description: Weegodda lotta fun stuff this year!  Come chill out in *Igloo Obscura*, make a wish at The Wishing Well (until it burns Friday night), take pictures with friends at our updated LoF Dream Teams mural and fill up your water bottle at the Hydration Station!!

Events.Title: Capt. Zesty's Space-Age Tiki Lounge
Events.Description: Captain Zesty invites you for an exploration into Exotica, Space Age-Pop, Cocktail music and cool jazz from the 1940's through 1960's.  Don your finest Hawaiian shirt or smoking jacket and tune in to 103.3 FM 2 a.m. to 5 a.m. Thursday and Friday.

Events.Title: Community Clothing Swap: (One More Thing for Your Wardrobe)
Events.Description: Looking to revamp your wardrobe or for a quick costume change? Or did you pack too much and want to lighten your load? Whatever the case, we've got something for you! Come by each day from sun up to sun down and check out all that our community clothing swap has to offer. We've got clothes, shoes, accessories, and more! If you ask nicely, we might even roll out the runway so you can strut your new stuff.

Events.Title: Coffee Up In the Morning
Events.Description: Enjoy cowboy coffee served fired or iced.

Events.Title: Kitty & Monkey Champagne, Cookies, and Confessions
Events.Description: It's confession time! Come by Radio SGC Friday morning and enjoy some champagne and cookies while you read your deepest confessions on the air. If you want to remain anonymous drop off your confessions in our mail box at the station before Friday morning and we will read it for you.

Events.Title: Miss Kitty's Meow Mix
Events.Description: Tune in to Radio SGC for Miss Kitty's Meow Mix Friday morning for all things kitty and confessions. We will be serving up tasty kitty tunes to get your day started along with cookies and champagne. Miss Kitty and extra special guest Monkey will also be broadcasting your deepest darkest confessions.

Events.Title: Walkabout with Squish!
Events.Description:
Squish is the greatest burner. She collects a following wherever she goes. Squish likes to put the late night Burners to bed in the early morning hours and wake the others up. Squish is two years old.

Come walkabout with Squish during her morning rounds! We'll start when Squish wakes up and is ready to go. We'll go wherever Squish leads us. We'll end when Squish is done. We'll probably stop along the way. 

Sippy cups and snacks recommended.

Events.Title: Find a costume (or bring a costume)
Events.Description: Come try on a new you or leave a costume for another to find! We are all costumes, most of the time. (Sometimes we're out volunteering, sometimes there are extra surprises like cupcakes but you don't have to wear those unless you want to.) Stop by to chat about costumes, we love it! Will have at least a basic sewing kit on site to help out in a pinch.

Events.Title: Found & Lost*
Events.Description:
*Not a typo!
The Official Unofficial L&F @ LoF!
Found an item and don't know where it belongs? We'll try to find out!
Lost an item and aren't sure where to find it? We may have it or know who has it! Seek out or return items after the event via http://bit.ly/2pNJKUF

Events.Title: The 5 Tibetans - a daily yoga practice
Events.Description: The 5 Tibetan Rights of Rejuvenation is an ancient practice for improved health and vitality. The great thing is that it takes only 10 minutes a day to complete. Come join Yogi Renz and learn this ancient practice. We will learn the history and then go through the movements. Please bring a yoga mat, blanket, and a pair of blocks.

Events.Title: The Morning Dish by No Drama Pancake House
Events.Description: Every morning, except Sunday (F U no questions), the No Drama Pancake House serves up fantastic, fresh-made flapjacks from such savory salivations as gourds, grains, and even garlic. We provide a friendly start to your oncoming great day in a certified, bona-fide, sanctified drama-free environment. Plus we've got mimosas, and games! We'll be providing an early bird onsite brekkie for Wednesday AM too.

Events.Title: Arrakis Brunch
Events.Description: Fremen serving Melange Cakes (cinnamon Toast) and Spice Coffee (Chai tea). byo Stillsuit (cup)

Events.Title: "BUZZ OFF" KIDS MOOP PARADE
Events.Description:
Don't just bug out about MOOP,  join us for a flight around the esplanade to ward off litterbugs! Bring your bumblebees , ladybugs, and butterflies for a fun and educational journey as we stomp out MOOP together!
Light lunch and cookie decorating after the parade.

Events.Title: Carrot Dogs
Events.Description: Come enjoy a delicious roasted carrot dog served from 10am to Noon.

Events.Title: Kelly Bells' Friday Morning Funk
Events.Description: Back by popular demand!! (at least that's what I tell myself) For the 3rd consecutive year, I will be sharing 2 hours of classic and contemporary funk music to get your day off to a bootylicious start.

Events.Title: Kid's storytime
Events.Description: Come to Kid's Wonderland for an hour filled with delightful stories!

Events.Title: LOF mini Triathlon
Events.Description: You don't need to be a super star athlete to participate in this race! Meet us at the eggify (effigy) on Friday morning for a quick lap across the lake, then sprint back to the eggify, and lastly, bike a lap around the lake to finish. Finisher medals and prizes to all participants!

Events.Title: Mimosas
Events.Description:
Mimosa Fairy Fridaaaaay!!  Does this need an explanation? Come tell us your secrets at Just The Tip and I'll add an extra strawberry* ;)
*While supplies last."

Events.Title: The Breakfast Bar
Events.Description: What happens when you combine your passions for hearty nourishment and a solid morning buzz?  The Breakfast Bar! We will be serving fancy ass oatmeal and breakfast themed shots. Vegan options available! BYO spoon & dish please.

Events.Title: DIY Tattoo Station
Events.Description: Drink & Stitch is bring some supplies to make You the art! An interactive piece in which we supply the rubber stamps & ink and you are the canvas. The table will be set up in front of Village Not Sure each day whenever one of us sobers up enough to do so. It will remain in place till dark for your enjoyment.

Events.Title: Rejuvenation
Events.Description: Rejuvenation will be open Thursday, Friday and Saturday morning. We will supply pre-packaged Emergen-C, B vitamins and over the counter pre-packaged herbal supplements to aid weary burners who find themselves less-than-chipper the morning after.

Events.Title: The Intrigue of Hook Suspension
Events.Description: What is Hook Suspension all about? See, live and in person, the amazing feats of the human body. Discover the personal expansion and energy exchange that can be obtained through flesh hook suspension.

Events.Title: Duckies
Events.Description:
A pool of ducks with fun little prizes. Draw a shot or maybe a gift from The Man himself.  All handmade. When we run out of shots we start giving out kisses. Kid friendly with juice and snack prizes if they wanna pick out ducks for fun! 

This runs while we are in camp cooking or hanging out throughout the day. If someone is there they can help you check out our chill area for the ducks!

Events.Title: Naked Yoga
Events.Description: Come over to Camp Pleasure / Camp Safehouse and join us for a refreshing dose of "Naked Yoga", with our Camp Resident Yoga Instructor
Events.HumanLocation: Camp Pleasure / Camp Safehouse | Site F

Events.Title: Noon Yoga at the Teahouse
Events.Description: Deep Mysteries Teahouse hosts free yoga for the community, taught by some of Lucky Lakes' most experienced instructors. Bring a mat or blanket if you have one. Class duration will be in the range of 60-90 minutes each day.

Events.Title: Rage Yoga
Events.Description:
Metal. Whiskey. Yoga.

Let's get fucking hostile. We encourage profanity, obscure concert t-shirts, and guttural screaming. Bring your inner turmoil, and a yoga mat.

Events.Title: Scott Freeform Radio, featuring HeyU's "Tales from the Burn Side"
Events.Description: Tune into Radio SGC, 103.3FM, as Scott Free jumps genres, smashes formats, screws up segues and basically does whatever he damn well please. New this year: Scott Free and special guest HeyU tell tales of Regional Burns from all corners of the globe. Edutaining!

Events.Title: Syncytium Healing Hut OPEN
Events.Description: How about a massage, energy session, acupuncture or some other interesting session. Stop by the the Syncytium Healing Hut and talk with Sprites who will set you up with a the right healer for you.

Events.Title: Theme Camp Capture the Flag
Events.Location: All over Lakes! Participating theme camps
Events.Description: All theme camps are encouraged to participate! This is an Opt-In Only event; theme camps that want to participate should make sure to check-in at Valhalla and pick up a flag. Rules: One flag per camp. ONLY designated flags may be taken from a theme camp. This is a contact sport- players would be consenting to being non-sexual touching/tagging while attempting to steal a flag. Game ends at noon on Saturday, at which point players will bring their captured flags to Valhalla for a count and announcement of the winner. LET THE GAMES BEGIN!
Events.HumanLocation: All over Lakes! Participating theme camps

Events.Title: Understanding Electronics
Events.Description: A practical lesson in simple electronics. Our Lector, Red-Oculus, Explains the basics of Electronics using Analogies so anyone can understand concepts and uses. This Class is intended for the curious novice and/or artists who want to use electronic motors and lights in their art.

Events.Title: Bloody Mary Bar!
Events.Location: The Consortium of Indigent Mythological Creatures and Imaginary Bunnies
Events.Description: It's back! The Choose Your Own Adventure Bloody Mary Bar. If you're lucky, you've stumbled onto it before.  We provide the ingredients needed for you to make the most awesome bloody mary ever... because you make it, the bartenders don't.  Boozes, tomato juices, spices, veggies, cheeses! You bring the cup, Jessca and Kalika will bring the blood. Because fuck you, that's why.
Events.HumanLocation: The Consortium of Indigent Mythological Creatures and Imaginary Bunnies | Site C

Events.Title: Daydreaming
Events.Description: Come out to play with the dreamers this afternoon. Customize your own parasol or umbrella at the Shade Creation Station, or take a loaner out for a spin. Transform your trash into art with a Moop Mobile! Or try the latest craze, Experimental Dream Capture. Requirements: a dream story and an open mind. Be advised, dream capturing is a delicate art, subject to changes in the wind. Open times were announced in last night?s dream. If you?ve already forgotten, check the sign by the garden gate.

Events.Title: Dino Drawing Lessons
Events.Description: Come to the Dino Dome for some creative dinosaur time. Our resident cartoonist, Griz, will be teaching dinosaur drawing. We have a bunch of paper, pens, crayons, and colored pencils to soothe your need for paleolithic artwork.

Events.Title: Learn to DJ lesson
Events.Description: Begin with the basics; BPM & Beat matching, then moving on to  programs. Hands on, guided practice followed by open decks.

Events.Title: Magic: The Gathering - Sphinx?s Booster Draft
Events.Description: The Sphinx brings you a Magic booster draw with the Amonkhet deck. There will be space for eleven contenders to do battle with a gifted set! Sphinx Darek will be hosting.

Events.Title: Ranger Group Photo
Events.Description: Annual group photo, for all 2017 Ranger volunteers. Wear your khaki best!

Events.Title: Spritz and Wine Spritzers
Events.Description: Cool down in the shade with a wine spritzer (or ice water as needed) and enjoy our refreshing cooling station amenities!

Events.Title: Tarot Card Readings
Events.Description: Tarot reader, Cristy, believes that tarot is not about divining the future, but gaining a better understanding of the energies surrounding your present. Bring questions about any aspect of your life and delve deeper with her into the meaning behind your cards.

Events.Title: Tarot Tequila and Cookies
Events.Description: Mystical Mike and Will Love are experienced explorers of the Mystical Tarot.  Sit down for a reading, hoist a shot of fine tequila and/or scarf down a home made cookie.   The more you open up to the cards, the more you insight into your own life you will gain.

Events.Title: Trapeze Demo and Lesson
Events.Description: Come join us in the Hullabaloo village and try your hand on the trapeze! Andrea will show you some of her skills and teach you some of your own. All skill levels welcome.

Events.Title: Dr. Boom's Explosion of  Science Show
Events.Description: What is fire? What is gravity?  What is the HIgg's field and what is the superconducting supercollider? These, and other mysteries of the universe are revealed in Dr. Boom's explosive exposition. {I am a science teacher and have done Fire and Science demonstrations.  Nothing bigger than a candle for flames and a potato cannon to explain combustion and gravity. The demonstrations have been performed in elementary schools and are safe, but satisfying in their effect}

Events.Title: Beach Time Thai Massage: For Deep Relaxation
Events.Description: Join Roman on the yoga beach for Beach Time Thai Massage: For Deep Relaxation.

Events.Title: Day-Drink Lip-Sync
Events.Description: Have you been singing along in the car for years? Dancing around the house? Both? We know you've got the moves, and you know the words (well, enough to get away with it). Come "perform" some crowd-favorite songs at the Odditorium. Nervous? Liquid courage is, well, encouraged. Rock out with a group or lip-sync a ballad to your honey - you'll always hit the high notes!

Events.Title: Dinosaur Cupcake Decorating with Bliss
Events.Description: Come decorate a dinosaur themed cupcake with a us. Frost a new ice(ing) age with us within Sally the Sauropod.

Events.Title: Gothic Coffee
Events.Description: Join the Gothee House for good company, goth/industrial dance music, and fresh hot coffee, dark like our souls. Coffee is served from early afternoon through the witching hour. Visitors are advised against signing contracts with magical creatures or following ghostly women into the woods.

Events.Title: Lakes of Fire Theatre Dress Rehearsal
Events.Description: Come one, come all to our dress rehearsal. Get a sneak peek of the traveling show, warm up your vocal chords, and make some great friends!

Events.Title: Mysterious Locked Chest: The Impossible Question
Events.Description: Rumors persist of a wise parking volunteer who knows the location of one of the keys to The Mysterious Locked Chest (?). However, he wields the most Brain Bending of trivia questions that you must answer first? do you dare subject your neurons to his quizzical onslaught?

Events.Title: Slushies!!!!
Events.Description: Join the Firewater Lounge from 2-4 pm for refreshing snow cones (or boozy slushies).  These refreshing treats will be available each day until supplies run out.  Join us to cool off.

Events.Title: The Syn Bar
Events.Description: Syncytium bar open daily from 2pm until 2am.  Beer and various mixed drinks.  Mixed drinks change daily.  Note: We are closed during the eggify burn.

Events.Title: Volunteer Appreciation Cookout!
Events.Description: All ages welcome! We want to appreciate the volunteers that secure the structure of Lakes of Fire by putting food in their beautiful faces!  If you're a Lakes of Fire 2017 volunteer please come on by the Dive Bar 2-4pm for some cookout food and refreshments.  All ages of volunteers welcome!  We cater to carnivores, omnivores, and herbivores!   We will have carts of food going out to volunteers on-shift who can't make it.  THANK YOU FOR VOLUNTEERING!!!

Events.Title: West Michigan Burners Meet Up
Events.Description: Calling West Michigan Burners! Join Burning Man Regional Contacts, Thor and Shirley for a cool beverage at the Tick Town bar. All attendees will be required to show their home location using the Michigan Hand technique!

Events.Title: Arctic Mermaid Picnic
Events.Description: Lounge with mermaids and merman and avoid the watery deeps afloat the coolest iceberg around!

Events.Title: Burlesque Workshop
Events.Description: Feeling Sexy? Want to show off? Stop by Camp Burnlesque! Come release your inner Diva as we shimmy, shake, flaunt, tease and twirl our tassels. With the help of the lovely Curly Kat you?ll be mastering all the iconic moves of burlesque in no time! Come pick out a sexy number in our costume tent and show off what you learned later tonight at our variety show!

Events.Title: Dickleback Bar
Events.Description: We have pickle back shots, just for you! Here's the catch, you gotta play drinko (at least once) to get 'em. Good luck, don't get shafted!

Events.Location: The Consortium of Indigent Mythological Creatures and Imaginary Bunnies

Events.Title: Erotica Readings
Events.Description: A place and time for people to bring in some of their favorite published erotica to share with a group. People can either read their found pieces themselves or request that another person do the reading for them if they would feel more comfortable that way. This will likely not be an incredibly serious event.

Events.Title: Igloo Obscura demonstration
Events.Description: Stop by Igloo Obscura to learn about the concept of *camera obscura* and how it works.

Events.Title: Margarita Pool
Events.Description: A kiddie pool full of margarita? Yes. Straws are provided and you don't need a cup. The drinks are in a POOL!

Events.Title: MUTANT RC VEHICLES SHOWTIME/PARADE
Events.Description: Presenting the first of many? Mutant RC Vehicles. You are invited to take the RC fun of your childhood and combine it with burning man culture and design your very own Mutant RC Vehicle!  Come watch, drive or create something strange and come play. Parade and show time (check the what, where, when or look for signage). Let burners take it for ?a test drive?.

Events.Description: Come play!  Hullabaloo Village is hosting field games. Challenge others to a game of tug of war, red rover, or duck duck goose!  We will have groupings for adults and children.  Also a great time to come play on The Fort's slide, swing, trapeze bar, aerial silk, climbing rope ladder and climbing ramp! All this among other playful activities we have for you. We'll have music going all day/night.  Come get a drink from the Bubble Bar!

Events.Title: Tyler the Typhoon?s Flow Warrior Congregation
Events.Description: Join Tyler the Typhoon of the hoop tribe  and come meet fellow flow warriors. Share your moves and techniques. This will be a great time to express your love for the power of flow! Any flow props are welcome! The more the merrier.

Events.Title: Acro Yoga Jam

Events.Title: Lakes of Fire Camp Famous Naked Twister

Come one come ALL, down to Camp Pleasure / Camp Safehouse on Friday Afternoon ! !

Events.Title: The Hunting of the prey Ice nation Scientists.
Events.Description:
Thursday, Friday and Saturday at Noon, 4pm, 8 pm, and midnight at the Fire Nation Dome floating on the lake. One hour events.

Events.Description: Veggie burritos are a dietary mainstay of the Hippie subspecies.  We make killer veggie burritos.

No worries friends, we did the schlepping for you!  This is an open jam for musicians of all interests and ability levels. Events.Title: Lakes of Fire Newbie Orientation
Events.Description: You've memorized the 10 Principles and read the entire survival guide (twice). Now, finally, you've arrived at Lakes of Fire. We're so glad you are here! Do you want some help getting the lay of the land? Have some burning questions you'd like answered? Your Greeter leads are thrilled to welcome you home, give you some tips, answer your questions and help set you on the path to awesome.

We'll give you the costumes and pasties if you promise to flirt, tease, and take it off for us! Newbies to burlesque and the stage are highly encouraged to participate. Burlesque not your thing? Events.Title: Camp Pleasure  / Camp Safehouse MASSAGE PARTY

Join us in breaking some bread, drinking a little wine (or grape juice for the kiddos or those who enjoy non-alcoholic beverages), and lighting a candle. Join us for a parade around the lake! Please come dressed as a creature of your choosing, whether that be an Animal Onesie, Dinosaur, or Faerie outfit. The colors and patterns change every few minutes; stick around to see what you can create!

Events.Description: Succumb to the Green Fairy with Gothee.  Share our Absinthe ritual. This is traditionally accompanied with discussion and merriment. Sample what Van Gogh and Manet used to drink. Scalpels for ears not provided. You are crazy already.

Events.Description: Who doesn't love bubbles!? Be mesmerized by the beauty of soap bubbles, and  create your own magical temporary spheres with your friends.

Events.Description:
Looking for a new buddy? Not sure what to do? Come make a new buddy at the Brand New Buddy Bench!

It's simple! Hover near it; sit, stand, dance! Wait for someone else to hover, too! When they do, FAH-DAH, a BNB!

Events.Title: Bubble Bar
Events.Description: Over in Hullabaloo Village the crews from Scrubby's Angels and The Fort will be mixing some bubbly concoctions to wet your whistle, we specialize in cocktails mixed with  your favorite Michigan mixers. Our bar will be open during all posted Hullabaloo, Scrubby's Angels, and Fort events. Join us for a nighttime dance party or random hammock hanging afternoons.You never know what might be poppin' at the Bubble Bar.   BYOC (Bring your own cup).

Events.Title: Burner Blanket Painting
Events.Description: Stop by and decorate a blanket for a burner in need! Did you forget your blanket? Need something warm to snuggle in? Stop by and we will provide you with an awesome gift from your burner family.

Events.Title: Canned Ham Camp
Events.Description:
It's all about the ham.  We eat ham, we live in a ham, we love ham.
Our camp is centered on our 1957 Classic Canned Ham Camper.  Please pay us a visit and we'll give you a tour.

Events.Title: Casual Misfortune Telling
Events.Description: The Gypsies are most EXCELLENT at telling your misfortune! Stop on by anytime we're in camp and request to have your runes interpreted, your palm read, your cards deciphered. Remember that we are professionals and definitely NOT just making random stuff up about you for our own amusements.

Events.Title: Compliment Tastings
Events.Description: Swing by the Lounge whenever you like and receive the compliment of your dreams. Our menu provides a variety of Compliment styles, sure to lift your spirits or leave you totally confused.

Events.Title: Desert Oasis Tea and Hookah Pit Stop
Events.Description:
Thirsty? Need a Pick-me-up or someone to talk to? Stop by our pit stop to refuel and relax, before continuing on your journey. Throughout the days, we will offer up some tea or start a session of hookah. You are more than welcome to join us and take in the views!

If the stars align and paths cross, there may even be an opportunity to have your Tarot read by one of our residents!

Events.Title: Found In the Wild Erotica Contests
Events.Description:
Burners will be able to submit excerpts from published erotica matching daily themes. People will be able to wander by at their leisure before voting closes to vote on what tales are their favorites and best fit the themes to choose the winner of a small prize. Please have the author's name or username and the name of the piece written on the back of your excerpt. Also, please do not bring your own work for the contests. It is surely masterful and it would be unfair!

Located in the Art Hub pine forest near the entrance to Lakes of Fire. Featuring the Dead Letter Office and the Memorial Room (an installation to honor those who have passed away.)
Events.HumanLocation: Pine Forest between Gate and Greeters

Events.Title: Gaming With The Gods
Events.Description: Stop in any time to join a table or yard game of your choice. Table games will be under the tent and yard games by the bar; come while away an hour in play!

Events.Title: GiGi
Events.Description:
GiGi, formerly incarnated as the Celestial Firefly, will be returning in a new form this year.
What will it be?
We don't even really know.
Watch the lake; watch for flames and we'll both find out.

Events.Title: Hookah and Tea at The Den
Events.Description: Stop by and chill with us at The Den. We will periodically serve tea and offer hookah. Relax with calming light and music, and check out the compliment lounge while you're here!

Events.Title: Lounge of the Gods
Events.Description: The Lounge has expanded with more space to recline and rest your weary warrior bones upon the lush fur-covered inflatable. Fellow Vikings will tell you the tales of the heroes and gods of days gone by while you sip mugs of glogg, and prepare for Ragnarok by sharpening your skills at hammerschlagen.

Events.Title: Love, Light, Music, More
Events.Description: Stop by Lux Ephemera during the day to fill your cups with floral-essence waters [we plan on offering Rose and Neroli], make a buddy, or just hang out in our lawn.  Come back and see us in the dark, though... we transform into a rainbowlightshinelovetimemusicshrine... we think it's worth checking out.  WE LOVE YOU!

Events.Title: Mama Boodles' Spunyun Hut
Events.Description: And so it came that Mama Boodles befriended the Ice Fairies, providing them a comfortable home to rest and frolic upon the shores of Lucky Lake. Using her interdimensional powers, Mama Boodles created a series of nesting hexayurts for her newfound minions, allowing them a peaceful respite from the Grand Climate War, and a convenient way to "recruit" new fairies, as well... Enter at your own risk...

Events.Title: Open Arts and Crafts
Events.Description: Within Sally the Sauropod you will find supplies for all your arts and crafts needs. We will have dinosaur themed coloring sheets, construction paper, glue sticks, craft scissors, crayons, pens, and colored pencils. Come drop by when you need to get some art time in.

Events.Title: Port Authority Camp
Events.Description:
Port Authority is a group dedicated to promoting boating and general water safety at Lakes of Fire. 
The "Pink PFD" program this year will place personal flotation devices and life vests at strategic locations around the lake for all to use. Boaters are reminded that every passenger on board your vessel must have access to a flotation device according to Michigan boating law.
The Lake is our Playa.
An informational booth will be located at the LOF Yacht Club. Stop by and learn more about what you can do to help.
Any supplies you can donate are much appreciated.
Events.HumanLocation: LoF Yacht Club (or find Pirate) | Site 35

Events.Title: Rights of Passage
Events.Description: The pooparazzi is back for a second year! Find us here, there, any where near a porta potty! We are here to celebrate your bodily functions! Are you lucky enough to feel poopular?

Events.Title: RVB camp games!
Events.Description: Red vs Blue camp games. Whether team Red or Blue the competition is fierce! Try fowling, balance games, board games, all the games.

Events.Title: Schnapps Shots Detour
Events.Description: Stop in for a sweet tasty shot of homemade schnapps, have a Native American Medicine card reading.  Be on the lookout  for the minibar and Camp Mascot!

Events.Title: Sphinx?s Menagerie
Events.Description: Come borrow a trusty steed from our floaty corral to aid you on your lake-bound adventures! We?ll be offering all manner of beasties for your buoyancy assistance needs. We do ask that you kindly return your creature to its paddock for the night when you?ve finished your aquatic cavorting.

Events.Title: Strip With Style!
Events.Description: You look great with your clothes on, and great with your clothes off. Learn to look great in between, because it's hard to impress the cutie in the camp next door with your foot caught in your pant leg. No clothing is too strange. If you can put it on, Burnlesque's own Action will show you how to take it off. You can find him at the Burnlesque Camp, or wandering around Lucky Lake throughout the event.

Events.Title: Take a Book, Leave a Book
Events.Description: Browse the books of the Lucky Lake Burner Library and choose a textual friend to take home and cuddle. (We do mean books!) Or, chat with a librarian, get a book recommendation, or take a stern shushin' for the road.

Events.Title: The Flow Project
Events.Description:
The Flow Project is setup to provide a welcoming space both visually and musically for participants to express their flow; whether it be dancing, spinning fire/hoops/poi, or what have you.. Our user friendly Flow Stage, stripper pole optional, will be available for open use. White gas will be provided for participants as a gift, as well as safeties if need be. Although we encourage radical self reliance. 

DJs will be spinning night and day. Chill vibes by day full on rager style vibes by night. Come kick it with us!!

Events.Title: The Huggery
Events.Description: Hugs served fresh and hot all day every day. Looking for that special hug for you or a friend? Come and visit the Huggery! We have an extensive menu of classic and specialty hugs as well as daily specials. Don't see what you want? Make a request and we'll do our best to fulfill it! Nobody is at the Huggery when you get there? You're hired! Step around to the other side of the counter and give out dem hugs!

After housekeeping changes the linens and restores cleanliness, the room will be open for another night.
