Events.Description: Hot chocolate and old cartoons, a good way to start a Saturday morning.

Events.Title: Brunch of the Gods
Events.Description: A breakfast worthy of the gods. Home cured bacon, fried up hot and crispy, served by a Viking in a pig hat. Put it in your face! Bloody Mary?s served with the freshest condiments, Mimosa?s & Screw Drivers to quench your thirst. Plus, non-alcoholic beverages for the kiddos. Stop, sit, eat, sip.

Events.Title: Carrot Dogs
Events.Description: Come enjoy a delicious roasted carrot dog served from 10am to Noon.

Events.Title: LNT the The Gifting Tree & Collect Gifts!
Events.Description: Help us LNT and collect your gifts!!  We painted the totems, then we lit them on fire, NOW come and dig them up as we LNT "The Gifting Tree" Wee-Effigy.  The effigy burn scar at North Beach needs to be cleaned up.  We are looking for some adults to help us as we pull the still warm clay pieces out of the ashes from the night before.  Kids can help us to brush off the totems and lay them out for folks to take a gift.  Come and help us clean up gifts for our community.
Events.HumanLocation: Wee-Effigy Burn Site (Firewater Lounge) | Site B

Events.Title: Saturday Morning Radio Cartoons
Events.Description: We may not have TV at LoF, but that doesn't mean we don't have cartoons! Tune your radio to 103.3FM as Dr Kilovolt plays an hour of music and sound clips for kids of all ages, plus a live radio theater skit at 10:30.

Events.Title: The Morning Dish by No Drama Pancake House
Events.Description: Every morning, except Sunday (F U no questions), the No Drama Pancake House serves up fantastic, fresh-made flapjacks from such savory salivations as gourds, grains, and even garlic. We provide a friendly start to your oncoming great day in a certified, bona-fide, sanctified drama-free environment. Plus we've got mimosas, and games! We'll be providing an early bird onsite brekkie for Wednesday AM too.

Events.Title: "You Donut Know How Much I Love You" Party
Events.Description: You Donut Know How Much We Love You until you stop by Cult of Janky Saturday morning for some donuts and love!

Events.Title: 20 min one-on-one Reiki sessions
Events.Description: 20 min Reiki sessions between 11 and 1 for those who desire some healing vibes to cleanse and lift up your spirit. Sign up sheet will be posted in the temple.

Events.Title: DIY Tattoo Station
Events.Description: Drink & Stitch is bring some supplies to make You the art! An interactive piece in which we supply the rubber stamps & ink and you are the canvas. The table will be set up in front of Village Not Sure each day whenever one of us sobers up enough to do so. It will remain in place till dark for your enjoyment.

Events.Title: Find a costume (or bring a costume)
Events.Description: Come try on a new you or leave a costume for another to find! We are all costumes, most of the time. (Sometimes we're out volunteering, sometimes there are extra surprises like cupcakes but you don't have to wear those unless you want to.) Stop by to chat about costumes, we love it! Will have at least a basic sewing kit on site to help out in a pinch.

Events.Title: Rejuvenation
Events.Description: Rejuvenation will be open Thursday, Friday and Saturday morning. We will supply pre-packaged Emergen-C, B vitamins and over the counter pre-packaged herbal supplements to aid weary burners who find themselves less-than-chipper the morning after.

Events.Title: Breakfast and Baptisms!
Events.Description: Come fill your stomach with breakfast treats and have your soul cleansed in Lucky Lake! (Totally non-denominational and just for fun.)

Events.Title: Daydreaming
Events.Description: Come out to play with the dreamers this afternoon. Customize your own parasol or umbrella at the Shade Creation Station, or take a loaner out for a spin. Transform your trash into art with a Moop Mobile! Or try the latest craze, Experimental Dream Capture. Requirements: a dream story and an open mind. Be advised, dream capturing is a delicate art, subject to changes in the wind. Open times were announced in last night?s dream. If you?ve already forgotten, check the sign by the garden gate.

Events.Title: Duckies
Events.Description:
A pool of ducks with fun little prizes. Draw a shot or maybe a gift from The Man himself.  All handmade. When we run out of shots we start giving out kisses. Kid friendly with juice and snack prizes if they wanna pick out ducks for fun! 

This runs while we are in camp cooking or hanging out throughout the day. If someone is there they can help you check out our chill area for the ducks!

Events.Title: Meat of the Gods (Taste of Lakes): Capture The Flag WINNER Announced
Events.Description: We crown the winner of Capture the Flag and feast on mouth-watering, hand cured and hand stuffed meats. Bring a dish to compliment the meats, or bring your meats to participate in the Great Meat Off Competition. All are welcome!

Events.Title: Noon Yoga at the Teahouse
Events.Description: Deep Mysteries Teahouse hosts free yoga for the community, taught by some of Lucky Lakes' most experienced instructors. Bring a mat or blanket if you have one. Class duration will be in the range of 60-90 minutes each day.

Events.Title: PARTYoga
Events.Description: What can we say...  It's just good for you!  Come stretch out the kinks after a long night of drinking, dancing or whatever.  Bring a mat if you have one, or we will have a few lying around. Mimosas optional but highly encouraged.

Events.Title: Syncytium Healing Hut OPEN
Events.Description: How about a massage, energy session, acupuncture or some other interesting session. Stop by the the Syncytium Healing Hut and talk with Sprites who will set you up with a the right healer for you.

Events.Title: Acro Yoga Workshop
Events.Description: Looking for a fun and challenging way to bond with your person, people, friend, camp mate ... or a complete and total stranger? Join us for a beginner/intermediate Acro yoga workshop and learn the fundamentals of the practice and how to work toward creating a basic flow. Depending on who shows up, we will be prepared to teach the basics for newbies, offer technique sharpening for intermediate acroyogis, or be available to spot for experienced practitioners who want to work on some new or more advanced postures. Bring a partner or come alone to play with someone new!

Events.Title: Scrubby Parade!
Events.Description: Come strut your stuff with Scrubby and his camp of Angels! Join us as we do a lap and get folks twerked up for the following Twerk Off at Hullabaloo village.   Throw on  some booty shorts and start with us in Hullabaloo Village or join in as we pass!

Events.Title: Dino Drawing Lessons
Events.Description: Come to the Dino Dome for some creative dinosaur time. Our resident cartoonist, Griz, will be teaching dinosaur drawing. We have a bunch of paper, pens, crayons, and colored pencils to soothe your need for paleolithic artwork.

Events.Title: Dragon Dick?s House of Happy Endings
Events.Description: Here at Valhalla we are proud of our Dragon Dick?s titillating finger strokes. Come on over and just relax. Dragon Dick will do the rest. *Maybe longer if the Dragon Dick can keep it up.

Events.Title: Ecstatic Dance & Cacao Activation
Events.Description: You are invited to join Roman and Nick for a special journey at Camp Natural Wonder's temple where we'll set intentions for the burn night. The sacred plant medicine cacao will help us flow through guided movement exercises into a free-form Ecstatic Dance. Express yourself however you wish in the conversation-free dance space, supported by guidelines of consent.

Events.Title: OddBrunch
Events.Description: Who doesn't love brunch? People who get up to make it first thing in the morning, that's who. Come by for some delicious food cooked on a much more... reasonable schedule. Plenty of veggie options provided!

Events.Title: Spritz and Wine Spritzers
Events.Description: Cool down in the shade with a wine spritzer (or ice water as needed) and enjoy our refreshing cooling station amenities!

Events.Title: Tarot Card Readings
Events.Description: Tarot reader, Cristy, believes that tarot is not about divining the future, but gaining a better understanding of the energies surrounding your present. Bring questions about any aspect of your life and delve deeper with her into the meaning behind your cards.

Events.Title: Tarot Tequila and Cookies
Events.Description: Mystical Mike and Will Love are experienced explorers of the Mystical Tarot.  Sit down for a reading, hoist a shot of fine tequila and/or scarf down a home made cookie.   The more you open up to the cards, the more you insight into your own life you will gain.

Events.Title: Bubble Tea
Events.Description: Delicious flavored tea with tapioca pearls. Come get some while supplies last!

Events.Title: Circus Playtime
Events.Description: This is an open play session for those that wish to collaborate and experience Circus Arts from walking on a tightwire to swinging on a trapeze bar. Come and explore and play with fellow circus people.

Events.Title: Gothic Coffee
Events.Description: Join the Gothee House for good company, goth/industrial dance music, and fresh hot coffee, dark like our souls. Coffee is served from early afternoon through the witching hour. Visitors are advised against signing contracts with magical creatures or following ghostly women into the woods.

Events.Title: Lakes of Fire Theatre Traveling Show
Events.Location: All over Lakes! Participating theme camps
Events.Description: Lakes of Fire Theatre is taking our show on the road! Starting at Camp Rechargec and ending at Bikes and Brew. Have a set list of favorites from musicals across wide swaths of space and time. Always looking for more chorus members! Have costumes, props, a stage and speakers! Let us entertain you, you entertain others and/or you radically entertain yourself!
Events.HumanLocation: All over Lakes! Participating theme camps

Events.Title: Mermaid Meetup
Events.Description: Calling all merfolk! Meet at the lily pads at Camp Natural Wonder for a mermazing hangout and fintastic photoshoot!

Events.Title: Show Me Your Bubble Twerk Off
Events.Description: Shake it don't break it!  Come and shake your butt in Hullabaloo Village. Scrubby's Angels will be teaching ya'll how to twerk! Don't look like a rap guys girlfriend (or boyfriend)? No worries, all ability levels welcome. Guided by tunes from Scrubby Bubble we will show you how to bounce yours.  Felling fierce after that twerk lesson? Been a pro for years? Enter the Twerk Off! You just may win the big Bubble prize!

Events.Title: Slushies!!!!
Events.Description: Join the Firewater Lounge from 2-4 pm for refreshing snow cones (or boozy slushies).  These refreshing treats will be available each day until supplies run out.  Join us to cool off.

Events.Title: The Syn Bar
Events.Description: Syncytium bar open daily from 2pm until 2am.  Beer and various mixed drinks.  Mixed drinks change daily.  Note: We are closed during the eggify burn.

Events.Title: Dr. Boom's Explosion of  Science Show
Events.Description: What is fire? What is gravity?  What is the HIgg's field and what is the superconducting supercollider? These, and other mysteries of the universe are revealed in Dr. Boom's explosive exposition. {I am a science teacher and have done Fire and Science demonstrations.  Nothing bigger than a candle for flames and a potato cannon to explain combustion and gravity. The demonstrations have been performed in elementary schools and are safe, but satisfying in their effect}

Events.Title: Burnlesque Figure Drawing Werkshop
Events.Description: Get loose and get lost in pure line and color! Join Kat at Camp Burnlesque to explore gestural drawings and blind contour portraits. Booze, Boobs, Wacky costumes, and weird doodles. Does it get any better? No, no it doesn't.

Events.Title: Cuddle Party!
Events.Description:
An educational and experiential workshop on consent, boundaries and healthy intimate non-sexual touch (AKA Cuddling). Come get an oxytocin high! You MUST attend the first hour (3-4pm) to participate but the cuddling will continue for an undetermined amount of time-usually a few hours.

This event is not explicit. It is very G/PG rated yet due to the nature of consent itself it is for age 18 and over participants.

Events.Title: Dickleback Bar
Events.Description: We have pickle back shots, just for you! Here's the catch, you gotta play drinko (at least once) to get 'em. Good luck, don't get shafted!

Events.Title: Erotica Readings
Events.Description: A place and time for people to bring in some of their favorite published erotica to share with a group. People can either read their found pieces themselves or request that another person do the reading for them if they would feel more comfortable that way. This will likely not be an incredibly serious event.
Events.HumanLocation: Lucky Lake Burner Library | Site K11

Events.Title: 'Murica Party
Events.Description: Celebrate ?Murica ! Join us and show off your Stars & Stripes fashion. Celebrate with Color Your World traveling coloring books, barcoding, refreshments with electrolytes (it?s what plants crave), and good ol? fashioned treats at Village Not Sure.

Events.Title: Nachos & Beer happy hour
Events.Description: Yum! BYOCP (bring your cup & plate)

Events.Title: Recess- Field Games
Events.Description: Come play!  Hullabaloo Village is hosting field games. Challenge others to a game of tug of war, red rover, or duck duck goose!  We will have groupings for adults and children.  Also a great time to come play on The Fort's slide, swing, trapeze bar, aerial silk, climbing rope ladder and climbing ramp! All this among other playful activities we have for you. We'll have music going all day/night.  Come get a drink from the Bubble Bar!

Events.Title: The Decommodified Bottle Share
Events.Description: a celebration of beer and camaraderie.  camp me & you invites all to a bottle share that aims to examine the great yeasty libation we all love, while leaving the branding and hype at the door.  Bring a bottle to share, or stop on by for a sampling! All labels must be removed or taped off.

Events.Title: Tyler the Typhoon?s Flow Warrior Congregation
Events.Description: Join Tyler the Typhoon of the hoop tribe  and come meet fellow flow warriors. Share your moves and techniques. This will be a great time to express your love for the power of flow! Any flow props are welcome! The more the merrier.

Events.Title: Whirlwind's Flow Show
Events.Description: Hoops, poi, leviwand, staff, belly dance, fans...no matter the flow, this is your radio show!  Stop by The Secret Gentlemen's Club and show us what you got.   Get on air and share your tips and tricks, costuming & performance advice, or just bring your favorite toy/prop and pump up the (flow) jam.

Events.Title: Deep Fried Pickles
Events.Description:
Deep fried dill pickles, as well as other types of homemade pickles for your snacking pleasure. 
Come put our dickle in your mouth!

Events.Title: Lounge hours
Events.Description: Come chill and have a drink in the green dragon lounge, Jams till sundown Deep dark ultra lounge till morning

Events.Title: Mad Hatter High Tea
Events.Description: From intoxicatingly aromatic oolongs to tantalizing Turkish tea, it's time to get tea drunk in our dome of whimsy.  Expand your palate. Drink all the tea. Let the fun begin.

Events.Title: Snickering Tick la Taberno
Events.Description: Come spin the rueda and play our fun juegos! Tick Town te ama!  ALSO: PoliTICKS got you down? Feeling frustrated? We have just the TICKet!  Come smash our pi�atas!  We'll be hosting this event daily around siesta time! You won't want to miss it! ALSO ALSO: LaTicka Canta-longs are new this year, so come on down and join in!  These flash mob pop up sing-a-longs have been inspired by our infamous Ticker-Twirl "sing a song" category.  We're taking it to a whole new level!  Happening throughout each day and night!

Events.Title: Sphinx Phamily Pheud
Events.Description: A burner take on another classic game show! Sphinx Darek will be hosting. Sign up during the week at the Thirsty Sphinx for one of two teams to battle it out for the win! Or come spectate, and cheer on your favorite team! Our Survey Sphinxters will be circulating throughout the week to gather answers to LoF-themed questions!

Events.Title: The Hunting of the prey Ice nation Scientists.
Events.Description:
Thursday, Friday and Saturday at Noon, 4pm, 8 pm, and midnight at the Fire Nation Dome floating on the lake. One hour events.

Though we are loath to involve a culture as primitive as humanity in our affairs, we find ourselves in need of mercenaries to hunt the escaped Ice nation scientists we seek.

As is customary on your world, you will amply be paid in "swag" for your success.

Your targets are a trio of shape shifting researchers from the ice nation, who will be hiding among the revelers at this event. Join us in their Destruction.

Events.Title: Death Metal Yoga
Events.Description: Put the OM in doom and let Gothee House guide you through a set of yoga sequences while immersed in the soothing sounds of brutality and destruction. Bring your own yoga mat.

Events.Title: Spanks & Dranks
Events.Description:
Come by Camp Safehouse  for some carnal fun mixed with libations.

We will be offering spankings from a variety of paddles, crops, whips and other  objects of punishment.  Or maybe you would like to be tied or placed in the stocks.  Whatever your kink or curiosity level we can handle it!
 There will be a wide and varied selection of spirits so come on out and join us.
Events.HumanLocation: Camp Pleasure / Camp Safehouse | Site F

Events.Title: Twisty Tunes with DJ Trailblazer
Events.Description: Much excitement abounds as your mindtrain gets thrown down new auditory pathways... time to get twisty!  DJ Trailblazer (MZRD) will be performing a two-hour set of mind-warping Hear-fun for you to put in your listen holes while you get ready for conclave/effigyburn!  SO!... while you're picking out the last bits and bobs for your costume, and corralling your camp-mates to get ready for the rest of burn night be sure to tune into Radio SGC to catch the vibe... I love you all

Events.Title: Pre-Burn Fashion Show
Events.Description: Get your glam on early and stop by Odditorium on your way to the burn-our stage will be transformed into a glitzy catwalk! Push the paparazzi aside and stomp the runway lookin fierce AF in your best look, the one you saved for last. Or, stop by just to ?ooooh? and ?aaahhh? at all the otherworldly fashions your fellow travelers have put on for the main event. Why be a sparkle pony when you can be a glitter gorgon?! Bring a surprise.

Events.Title: BOOM!!!
Events.Description: Did you hear that?  It is approximately 8:30pm on Saturday and conclave for the big show is going to start in about 30 minutes.

Events.Title: Drunken sunset yoga
Events.Description: Find us! We will be drunk, somewhere, around sunset, everyday, doing yoga.

Events.Title: BOOM!!! again
Events.Description: It is about 8:45pm and fire spinning around the effigy is going to start in about fifteen minutes.

Events.Title: Eggify Burns, Phoenix Reborn
Events.Description:
A long time ago, like, last year, a Dragon was defeated and burned. In his wake, he left an Egg, and this in turn was left behind by LNT. Over the year, this fire-born Egg grew, and inside a shard of ice was frozen a Phoenix, locked in stasis. 

Tonight the last of that ice will melt and the Bird will hatch, in fire and radiance. And the Phoenix will be reborn.

Conclave starts at 9pm. Listen to the sounds of the Boom

Events.Title: Lumokinesis
Events.Description:
Lumokinesis is an interactive Kinect-powered art performance space, where your body is projected onto a screen and is transformed in mind-bending ways; your body and motion are in charge of creating your own surreal, vivid experience. The colors and patterns change every few minutes; stick around to see what you can create! 

Stop by every day when the moon replaces the sun to play and be entertained by pop up performances. 

From the same team who brought you the crazy interactive problem solving installation known as The Experiment!

Events.Title: Pyrosonica
Events.Description:
Pyrosonica is an ancient fire key thought to be lost eons ago. The key is only activated with certain magical tones, with each different tone unlocking another icy door in this realm. It has been entrusted to the inhabitants of "Hullabaloo Village" to make certain all revelers have full access to these Firey and Icy lands....
Come to "Hullabaloo Village" to warm yourself by the fire key in its activated state after dark and marvel at the display.

Events.Title: Absinthe Ritual
Events.Description: Succumb to the Green Fairy with Gothee.  Share our Absinthe ritual. We have authentic Spanish absinthe containing Thujone (one of the active ingredients in wormwood) and an artisanal absinthe fountain made by one of our members. Your absinthe prep will take 10-15 minutes, depending on how much absinthe your hosts imbibed before you arrived. The ritual is just a suggestion, and you can drink absinthe any way you like. This is traditionally accompanied with discussion and merriment. Sample what Van Gogh and Manet used to drink. Scalpels for ears not provided. You are crazy already.

Events.Title: BURN Afterparty with BenmeR & Friends
Events.Description: The effigy has burned and now its time to let loose!  Join BenmeR, his fellow DJ friends and the SGC for some grand celebrations to ring in the New Burn!  We got all the fancy that you will need to feel fresh and funky on Burn night!

Events.Title: Mysterious Soul Bearing Shadow Shroud of Dancing Like No One Is Watching
Events.Description: The name says it all! There will be lights. There will be sounds. There will be big red buttons. What do the big red buttons do? Come find out! While you?re here bust a move and show me what you got.  Express yourself and bear your soul from behind the curtain where no one can see you, but everyone can watch your shadow jive.

Events.Title: Pretty Big Fire
Events.Description: There's this thing that burns every year I heard. Follow the clues.

Events.Title: Glow Fowling
Events.Description: Glow Fowling, not sure what that is? Glowing football , bowling...it?s awesome!

Events.Title: Jurassic Mushroom Homecoming
Events.Description: We are hosting a homecoming dance after the big burn. This is a Jurassic Mushroom theme event, we will be crowning a King and Queen, and will only last 2 hours! Formal wear required!(extras encouraged and provided)

Events.Title: Phoenix Rising - Eggify Post-Party
Events.Description:
The Eggify has burned, and the Phoenix has been reborn. Join us at Syncytium to celebrate with fire and drink the turning of this year's page of the Story-on-the-Lake. 

We live, we burn, we live again!

Events.Title: Steve...the poofer
Events.Description: Try him out, he?s a little toucheee, but oh so pretty

Events.Title: UV Black light Bar
Events.Description: Upper spectrum drinks such as Sangria in suspension where fruit defies gravity, color changing gin and vodka drinks. Unicorn champagne. Glowing alien brain hemorrhage shots, while supplies last. Wear the UV reactive outfit you packed.

Events.Title: You Pick It Double Feature
Events.Description: Lakes of Fire attendees will choose the films we show via a Facebook poll.

Events.Title: Zen Coal Garden
Events.Description:
Have you ever wanted to tend a garden of fire? Here's your opportunity. After the Eggify fire burns down, you can rake the coals and peacefully contemplate your transformative experience as you stare into the beautiful shimmering reality of slow combustion. 

Because this breaks up coals and makes LNT easier, if you come find one of the Eggify LNT leads the next day and let us know about how long you broke up and spread around coals for, we will count this as volunteer hours.

Events.Title: Brand New Buddy Bench
Events.Description:
Looking for a new buddy? Not sure what to do? Come make a new buddy at the Brand New Buddy Bench!

It's simple! Hover near it; sit, stand, dance! Wait for someone else to hover, too! When they do, FAH-DAH, a BNB! 

There will be a WWW with one of those AM/PM device things, some of those weird ice breaking questions (Not you Ice Nation, BNB ice), and of course a table for you to set your cup on and forget it, so you can come back and make ANOTHER BRAND NEW BUDDY!

Events.Title: BBQ & Community Smoker
Events.Description: The dcbbq will smoke and gift hundreds of pounds of delicious BBQ during LoF.  Look for the "Meat Wagon" cruising around the event.  Rules: The BBQ is ready whenever it's ready, and allow us to serve. Our dedicated community smoker is back in 2017 for use by the LoF community! Basic orientation is required; swing by camp and find Dev or an authorized dcbbq agent. Rules: We will not babysit your food, and we will not accept "donations" of unwanted meat/food. Brisket.

Events.Title: Beer O?Clock at the Thirsty Sphinx
Events.Description: Keep an eye out for the sign at the Thirsty Sphinx Bar! When the planets align and a Sphinx bartender emerges from the cosmos, the sign will go up at our bar and the sweet brewed nectar will flow! Bring your cup to share in the Sphinx?s liquid bounty - non-alcoholic beverages will also be offered.

Events.Title: Canned Ham Camp
Events.Description:
It's all about the ham.  We eat ham, we live in a ham, we love ham.
Our camp is centered on our 1957 Classic Canned Ham Camper.  Please pay us a visit and we'll give you a tour.

Events.Title: Casual Misfortune Telling
Events.Description: The Gypsies are most EXCELLENT at telling your misfortune! Stop on by anytime we're in camp and request to have your runes interpreted, your palm read, your cards deciphered. Remember that we are professionals and definitely NOT just making random stuff up about you for our own amusements.

Events.Title: Gallery In The Pines
Events.Location: Pine Forest between Gate and Greeters
Events.Description: Gallery in the Pines is an interactive community art gallery featuring artwork of all kinds - by our own community! Located in the Art Hub pine forest near the entrance to Lakes of Fire. Featuring the Dead Letter Office and the Memorial Room (an installation to honor those who have passed away.)
Events.HumanLocation: Pine Forest between Gate and Greeters

Events.Title: Gaming With The Gods
Events.Description: Stop in any time to join a table or yard game of your choice. Table games will be under the tent and yard games by the bar; come while away an hour in play!

Events.Title: GiGi
Events.Description:
GiGi, formerly incarnated as the Celestial Firefly, will be returning in a new form this year.
What will it be?
We don't even really know.
Watch the lake; watch for flames and we'll both find out.

Events.Title: Port Authority Camp
Events.Description:
Port Authority is a group dedicated to promoting boating and general water safety at Lakes of Fire. 
The "Pink PFD" program this year will place personal flotation devices and life vests at strategic locations around the lake for all to use. Boaters are reminded that every passenger on board your vessel must have access to a flotation device according to Michigan boating law.
The Lake is our Playa.
An informational booth will be located at the LOF Yacht Club. Stop by and learn more about what you can do to help.
Any supplies you can donate are much appreciated.
Events.HumanLocation: LoF Yacht Club (or find Pirate) | Site 35

Events.Title: Sphinx?s Menagerie
Events.Description: Come borrow a trusty steed from our floaty corral to aid you on your lake-bound adventures! We?ll be offering all manner of beasties for your buoyancy assistance needs. We do ask that you kindly return your creature to its paddock for the night when you?ve finished your aquatic cavorting.

Events.Title: The Flow Project
Events.Description:
The Flow Project is setup to provide a welcoming space both visually and musically for participants to express their flow; whether it be dancing, spinning fire/hoops/poi, or what have you.. Our user friendly Flow Stage, stripper pole optional, will be available for open use. White gas will be provided for participants as a gift, as well as safeties if need be. Although we encourage radical self reliance. 

DJs will be spinning night and day. Chill vibes by day full on rager style vibes by night. Come kick it with us!!

Events.Title: The Huggery
Events.Description: Hugs served fresh and hot all day every day. Looking for that special hug for you or a friend? Come and visit the Huggery! We have an extensive menu of classic and specialty hugs as well as daily specials. Don't see what you want? Make a request and we'll do our best to fulfill it! Nobody is at the Huggery when you get there? You're hired! Step around to the other side of the counter and give out dem hugs!

Events.Title: Weegodda Village on display...
Events.Description: Weegodda lotta fun stuff this year!  Come chill out in *Igloo Obscura*, make a wish at The Wishing Well (until it burns Friday night), take pictures with friends at our updated LoF Dream Teams mural and fill up your water bottle at the Hydration Station!!

Events.Title: Community Clothing Swap: (One More Thing for Your Wardrobe)
Events.Description: Looking to revamp your wardrobe or for a quick costume change? Or did you pack too much and want to lighten your load? Whatever the case, we've got something for you! Come by each day from sun up to sun down and check out all that our community clothing swap has to offer. We've got clothes, shoes, accessories, and more! If you ask nicely, we might even roll out the runway so you can strut your new stuff.

Events.Title: Collexdous
Events.Description: When you are breaking camp and packing away All The Things! Please remember us at Collexodus. We will be at the Greeters' station wishing you safe travels AND collecting Ready-to-Eat food in unopened packages for the volunteers who are remaining behind for Resto. Things to consider: individually wrapped salty snacks, cookies, snack bars. Food that can be eaten on the go. Cheese & lunch meats. Sunblock, cigarettes, & whiskey.

Events.Title: Eggify LNT
Events.Description:
Help us LNT the ashes of the departed Phoenix. Come earn your last couple volunteer hours for the week, and-or help us complete the last task of our responsibility as this year's builders. Many hands make for short work, and we'd truly appreciate any help. We start in the morning and work until it's done. 

What's left of Syncytium bar will help provide refreshments.

Events.Title: Find a costume (or bring a costume)
Events.Description: Come try on a new you or leave a costume for another to find! We are all costumes, most of the time. (Sometimes we're out volunteering, sometimes there are extra surprises like cupcakes but you don't have to wear those unless you want to.) Stop by to chat about costumes, we love it! Will have at least a basic sewing kit on site to help out in a pinch.

Events.Title: Found & Lost*
Events.Description:
*Not a typo!
The Official Unofficial L&F @ LoF!
Found an item and don't know where it belongs? We'll try to find out!
Lost an item and aren't sure where to find it? We may have it or know who has it! Seek out or return items after the event via http://bit.ly/2pNJKUF

Events.Title: Kelly Bells' Gospel Brunch
Events.Description: I got your Rock of Ages right here...

Events.Title: Kelly Bells' Sweet Home Chicago
Events.Description: As we pack up to head home, I celebrate mine; the beautiful city of Chicago. I will be playing songs about Chicago, as well as featuring Chicago musicians. There will be prizes!
